Package org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.output.nicells Description

This package contains nicells and related interfaces.
A nicell is a descendant of class NiOutCell which holds information in aggregated state, e.g. a NiOutCell is the result of putting together 0, 1 or more NiCell instances through an operation of reduction. The specification of this transformation depends on the measure the initial NiCells were generated by
Please note that reduction always happens within NiCell instances coming from the same entity, thus NiReportedEntity.getBehaviour() governs it all.
Being aggregated cells, NiOutCell and descendants lack many of the attributes of an ordinary disaggregated CellVisitor:
  • they lack coordinates
  • they lack metadata
  • they lack ownerIds
